5:
Whoa... So this is what towns on this 
world look like.
8:
Oh, uh, I meant... I've never seen 
a town with so many buildings.
11: The king's city is far larger.
13:
You. Don't talk until we're in the lord's 
house. People around here don't like 
beastfolk.
23:
I've only met two. Your friend and the 
hellcat. Why do you think he was 
turned into a freak—
26: Nadir?! Look, it's Nadir! He's alive!
31:
And in one piece. So... the hellcat 
wasn't there.
33:
But that means more of us are gonna 
be sent into the desert... and forced to 
look for him.
36:
No, I fought him. But those people 
saved me.
39:
Let's go. I need to take you to the Lord 
of the Oasis.
44: That's all I have to report.
48:
How very ironic. I sent you on a 
mission to KILL a beast...
50:
And you come scuttling back to my 
manor—with a mangy PET in tow.
54:
They defeated the hellcat out in the 
desert and—
56:
Have you forgotten? I despise soldiers 
who can't earn their keep.
67: Silence. Beasts are not meant to talk.
77:
Alk, enough! You must reason with 
him!
79:
...What did Nadir do that was so 
wrong?!
84:
He FAILED his mission, and he is a 
FAILURE as a soldier. It only seems just 
that I punish him.
89: He is not a failure. He is Nadir.
90: Release him. You are being illogical.
93:
And I can't perceive the logic behind 
YOUR actions. What is that boy to you 
anyways?
96:
If you're so set on saving him, bring 
me the head of the hellcat. We'll call it 
a little prisoner exchange.
104:
IF you bring me the head. Disappoint 
me, and I'll have you thrown into the 
dungeon for treason. I AM royalty, 
after all.
106:
Well, you defeated the hellcat once. 
I'm sure you can do it again...
113:
We have no choice but to listen to 
him. He has Nadir.
114:
...We must not set the lord of this land 
against us. He could impede our 
search for the World Flipper.
117:
So, that tiger's in the ruins to the 
north, right?
122: Do you believe he is actually evil?
126:
None of Nadir's wounds were caused 
by tooth or claw.
131:
...You know, when we were fighting, 
I got the feeling he didn't really want 
to hurt us.
134:
Then we capture him—alive. Are you 
with me?
143:
Mm... It's gonna be tough…
But it's worth a shot!
